Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Trim the @carrot{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Chop the @sweet potato{1} (no need to peel) into 2cm chunks.

Pop the aubergine, sweet potato and carrot onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle with the @baharat spice mix{1%tbsp}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. -- TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the veg on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through, then add the @baby plum tomatoes{125} to the tray to roast for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Roughly chop the @dill{1}(chopped, stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lemon{½}(zested and halved).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring regularly, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour the @water{240%ml}(for the bulgur) into the pan and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Tahini Yoghurt Dressing ==

Meanwhile, pop the @tahini{30%g} into a small #bowl{}. Mix in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @sugar{1%tsp}(for the dressing), then add a squeeze of lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.

Stir to combine, then mix in the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} until smooth. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Set the tahini dressing aside.

== Zhoug Bulgur ==

Once the bulgur wheat is cooked, stir through the @zhoug style paste{50%g}, lemon zest and half the dill.

Taste and season with salt and pepper. Add a squeeze of lemon juice if you'd like.

== To Serve ==

Once the vegetables are cooked, stir them through the bulgur wheat, then share between your plates.

Drizzle over the tahini dressing and sprinkle over the remaining dill. Enjoy!